											<section class="main bio authorbio">
							<h3 class="invis">Author bio</h3>
																																															<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/karen-pinchin/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_bottom" >
											<div class="container col3 ">
												<div class="col span2"><p>Karen Pinchin is an investigative journalist and trained chef whose food systems reporting has been supported by the Canada Council for the Arts, the Society of Environmental Journalists, and the Sloan Foundation. Author of <em>Kings of Their Own Ocean: Tuna, Obsession and the Future of Our Seas</em>, Karen lives, writes, and fishes in Dartmouth, Nova Scotia.</p></div>
												<div class="singlebioimage col nomobile"><img width="520" height="520" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/karenpinchin-520x520.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/karenpinchin-520x520.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/karenpinchin-150x150.jpg 150w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/karenpinchin-768x768.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/karenpinchin-900x900.jpg 900w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/karenpinchin.jpg 1000w" sizes="(max-width: 520px) 100vw, 520px" /></div>
